In our effort to protect our customer's data, we will no longer take or store credit card data in any manner within our systems. As of April 30, 2016 we will not accept credit card payments via e-mail, fax or standard mail. Please note, when contacting via phone it is not secure to leave credit card information on voice mail. We take our customers' security seriously and believe that this approach is in the best interest to protect our customers and our company alike.




Customers can return digital, non-subscription products outside of the 10 day refund policy if one of the following criteria is met and documentation is provided:

The class was dropped.
The wrong product was ordered (and re-order of the correct product occurred).
There were technical difficulties preventing usage.
Product was purchased under the wrong email address  (and re-order using correct e-mail occurred).
Duplicate order.
A physical access card purchased elsewhere.
The instructor decided to not use product

















